clicklock - screen locker for touch kiosk devices (based on slock)
==================================================================
If you need to catch the first touch event to prevent blind clicks on a
blanked touchscreen.


Requirements
------------
In order to build clicklock you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (clicklock is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install clicklock
(if necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running clicklock
-------------
Simply invoke the 'clicklock' command. To get out of it, press a any key or
click with mouse.
